# ATS Fit Backend - Root Environment Template
# ========================================================================
# This template provides an overview of all environment variables.
# Copy the appropriate config/env file based on your environment.
# ========================================================================

# Environment Selection
# Uncomment and set based on your deployment environment:
# NODE_ENV=development  # Use for local development
# NODE_ENV=staging      # Use for staging environment  
# NODE_ENV=production   # Use for production environment

# ========================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Do not put sensitive values in this root template file!
# ========================================================================
# Instead, use the environment-specific files in src/config/:
# - .env.dev for development (with actual values for local development)
# - .env.staging for staging (with ${VAR} placeholders for CI/CD)
# - .env.prod for production (with ${VAR} placeholders for Cloud Run)
# ========================================================================

# Quick Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy the appropriate template from src/config/
# 2. Rename it to match your environment (.env.dev, .env.staging, .env.prod)
# 3. Fill in the actual values (for development) or ensure Secret Manager is configured (for prod/staging)
# 4. Never commit files with real API keys or passwords to git

# For development setup:
# cp src/config/.env.dev.template src/config/.env.dev
# # Then edit src/config/.env.dev with your actual development values

# For production deployment:
# The production environment uses Google Secret Manager
# Run: ./scripts/setup/create-secrets.sh (after configuring actual secret values)

# Environment Variables Overview:
# ========================================================================
# Database: DATABASE_HOST, DATABASE_PORT, DATABASE_USERNAME, DATABASE_PASSWORD, DATABASE_NAME
# Redis: REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT, REDIS_PASSWORD
# JWT: JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRES_IN
# OpenAI: OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_MAX_RETRIES, OPENAI_RETRY_DELAY
# Anthropic: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES, CLAUDE_RETRY_DELAY
# AWS: AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, AWS_S3_BUCKET, AWS_REGION
# Performance: CACHE_TTL, MAX_CACHE_SIZE, PDF_TIMEOUT, MAX_FILE_SIZE
